pullsbody:
Fixes #111


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_
pull_commit_message:
Add Mozilla Code of Conduct file

Fixes #111.

_(Message COC002)_

pulltitle: Update Django to 1.11 and Mezzanine to 4.3
pullsbody:
Both Django and Mezzanine had security issues. (close MozillaFoundation/mofo-devops-private#144)

Changes:
- I removed "mezzanine.core.middleware.TemplateForDeviceMiddleware" and "mezzanine.core.middleware.TemplateForHostMiddleware" because they're deprecated,
- Changed "get_latest_by" by "ordering", a param that Django Rest Framework uses to order items on a page,
- Updated Heroku configuration. The post-deploy step is a review app feature only, we don't need to check if we're running in one or not.
pull_commit_message: Update django and mezzanine (security issue). Fix mezzanine warning.

pulltitle: update psycopg2 to the latest version
pullsbody:
I got this error while doing pip install requirements:

```Collecting psycopg2==2.6.2 (from -r requirements.txt (line 3))
  Downloading psycopg2-2.6.2.tar.gz (376kB)
    100% |████████████████████████████████| 378kB 2.9MB/s
    Complete output from command python setup.py egg_info:
    running egg_info
    creating pip-egg-info/psycopg2.egg-info
    writing pip-egg-info/psycopg2.egg-info/PKG-INFO
    writing dependency_links to pip-egg-info/psycopg2.egg-info/dependency_links.txt
    writing top-level names to pip-egg-info/psycopg2.egg-info/top_level.txt
    writing manifest file 'pip-egg-info/psycopg2.egg-info/SOURCES.txt'
    warning: manifest_maker: standard file '-c' not found

    Error: could not determine PostgreSQL version from '10.0'
```

Updating psycopg2 to the latest version fixed it.
pull_commit_message: update psycopg2 to the latest version

pullsbody:
Logic to GET all projects

To try and see if this works, you'll first need to add some data into the db. access your app through the admin interface and first add some Tags and Categories and then create a new Project with those tags and categories and finally add some Resource Links and attach them to the newly created project. Then, hit the `/projects/` route and you should see it work.

I'll probably need to clean up some of the permission stuff.

Logic to GET all projects

Then, hit the `/projects/` route and you should see it work.
